      "name": "",
      "username": "Alex",
      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2024-01-23T10:52:21.624Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Maybe Zwift has some tricks with their trainer.  Maybe they even send the signal even earlier to tell it to switch.  We send it 2 seconds before the interval which works reasonably ok for most trainers.   Since the delay is constant, and you use 5 seconds at the beginning and should gain 5 at the end, the duration should be ok, it\u2019s just your expectations as to when they occur end up being wrong.   You can only use our editor to have automated slope mode with our app.  If you want to create a feature request to allow slopes from intervals, my guess is others might vote for it as well.</p>",
